#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:28 src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Average dry thermal updraft strength near mid-BL height. Subtract glider "
"descent rate to get average vario reading for cloudless thermals. Updraft "
"strengths will be stronger than this forecast if convective clouds are "
"present, since cloud condensation adds buoyancy aloft (i.e. this neglects "
"\"cloudsuck\"). W* depends upon both the surface heating and the BL depth."
msgstr ""
"Gennemsnitlig trodløst termik optræk nært mid-BL højde. Træk gliders "
"descenthastighed fra dette for at få gennemsnitsvariometerleseningen hos "
"skyfri thermaler. Opdrætshastighederne vil være stærkere end denne prognose, "
"hvis konvektionsskyer er præsent, da skyens kondensation tilbyder yderligere "
"buoyans (dvs. dette ignorerer \"cloudsuck\"). W* afhænger af både "
"overfladevarmelse og BL-dybde."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:37
#, no-c-format
msgid "BL Wind spd"
msgstr "BL Vind hastighed"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The speed and direction of the vector-averaged wind in the BL. This "
"prediction can be misleading if there is a large change in wind direction "
"through the BL."
msgstr ""
"Hastigheden og retningen på den vektor-åndrerede vind i BL. Denne prognose "
"kan være fejlagtig, hvis der er en stor ændring af vindretning gennem hele "
"BL."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:42
#, no-c-format
msgid "H bl"
msgstr "H blås"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Height of the top of the mixing layer, which for thermal convection is the "
"average top of a dry thermal. Over flat terrain, maximum thermalling heights "
"will be lower due to the glider descent rate and other factors. In the "
"presence of clouds (which release additional buoyancy aloft, creating "
"\"cloudsuck\") the updraft top will be above this forecast, but the maximum "
"thermalling height will then be limited by the cloud base. Further, when the "
"mixing results from shear turbulence rather than thermal mixing this "
"parameter is not useful for glider flying."
msgstr ""
"Højden af topen af blandingslageret, hvilket for termikkonvektion er "
"gennemsnittet højde af et trodløst thermik. Over flate terræn vil maksimale "
"thermikflyvningshøjder være lavere på grund af gliders descenthastighed og "
"andre faktorer. I tilstedeværelse af skyer (som relaterer yderligere "
"buoyans, skabende \"cloudsuck\") vil opdrætshastigheds-toppen være over "
"denne prognose, men maksimale thermikflyvningshøjden vil da være begrænset "
"af skybasen. Desuden, når blandingsresultater fra shear turbulence i stedet "
"for termikkonvektion, er dette parameter ikke nyttig til gliderflyvning."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "dwcrit"
msgstr "dwkrit"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This parameter estimates the height above ground at which the average dry "
"updraft strength drops below 225 fpm and is expected to give better "
"quantitative numbers for the maximum cloudless thermalling height than the "
"BL Top height, especially when mixing results from vertical wind shear "
"rather than thermals. (Note: the present assumptions tend to underpredict "
"the max. thermalling height for dry conditions.) In the presence of clouds "
"the maximum thermalling height may instead be limited by the cloud base. "
"Being for \"dry\" thermals, this parameter omits the effect of \"cloudsuck\"."
msgstr ""
"Denne parameter estimerer højden over jord, hvor gennemsnitlig trodløst "
"optrækstrengde falder under 225 fpm og forventes at give bedre kvantitative "
"tal for maksimal skyfri thermikflyvningshøjde end BL Top-højden, specielt "
"når blandingsresultater fra vertikal vindshear i stedet for "
"termikkonvektion. (Bemærk: de nuværende antagelser tendere til at "
"underprædiktere maksimale thermikflyvningshøjden for trodløse "
"omstændigheder.) I tilstedeværelse af skyer kan maksimale "
"thermikflyvningshøjder i stedet være begrænset af skybasen. Da det er for "
"\"trodløse\" thermaler, ignorerer denne parameter effekten af \"cloudsuck\"."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "bl cloud"
msgstr "bl sky"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:53
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This parameter provides an additional means of evaluating the formation of "
"clouds within the BL and might be used either in conjunction with or instead "
"of the other cloud prediction parameters. It assumes a very simple "
"relationship between cloud cover percentage and the maximum relative "
"humidity within the BL. The cloud base height is not predicted, but is "
"expected to be below the BL Top height."
msgstr ""
"Denne parameter tilbyder en yderligere måde at vurdere formationen af skyer "
"indenfor BL og kunne bruges enten i samme eller stedet for de andre "
"skyprognoseparametre. Den antager en meget simpel relæsholdning mellem "
"skydekkeprocent og den maksimale relative luftfugtighed indenfor BL. "
"Skybasen højden prædikeres ikke, men forventes at være under BL Top-højden."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sfc temp"
msgstr "Overflade temperatur"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The temperature at a height of 2m above ground level. This can be compared "
"to observed surface temperatures as an indication of model simulation "
"accuracy; e.g. if observed surface temperatures are significantly below "
"those forecast, then soaring conditions will be poorer than forecast."
msgstr ""
"Temperaturen på en højde af 2 meter over jordniveauet. Dette kan "
"sammenlignes med observerede overfladetemperaturer som et indikator for "
"modellersimuleringspræcision; f.eks. hvis observerede overfladetemperaturer "
"er signifikant lavere end de foretalte, vil soaringstilstande være mindre "
"givende end foretalt."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:62
#, no-c-format
msgid "hwcrit"
msgstr "hvcrit"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:63
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This parameter estimates the height at which the average dry updraft "
"strength drops below 225 fpm and is expected to give better quantitative "
"numbers for the maximum cloudless thermalling height than the BL Top height, "
"especially when mixing results from vertical wind shear rather than "
"thermals. (Note: the present assumptions tend to underpredict the max. "
"thermalling height for dry conditions.) In the presence of clouds the "
"maximum thermalling height may instead be limited by the cloud base. Being "
"for \"dry\" thermals, this parameter omits the effect of \"cloudsuck\"."
msgstr ""
"Denne parameter estimerer højden, hvor gennemsnitlig trodløst optrækstrengde "
"falder under 225 fpm og forventes at give bedre kvantitative tal for "
"maksimal skyfri thermikflyvningshøjde end BL Top-højden, specielt når "
"blandingsresultater fra vertikal vindshear i stedet for termikkonvektion. "
"(Bemærk: de nuværende antagelser tendere til at underprædiktere maksimale "
"thermikflyvningshøjden for trodløse omstændigheder.) I tilstedeværelse af "
"skyer kan maksimale thermikflyvningshøjder i stedet være begrænset af "
"skybasen. Da det er for \"trodløse\" thermaler, ignorerer denne parameter "
"effekten af \"cloudsuck\"."

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "wblmaxmin"
msgstr "vblmaxmin"

#: src/Weather/Rasp/RaspStore.cpp:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Maximum grid-area-averaged extensive upward or downward motion within the BL "
"as created by horizontal wind convergence. Positive convergence is "
"associated with local small-scale convergence lines. Negative convergence "
"(divergence) produces subsiding vertical motion, creating low-level "
"inversions which limit thermalling heights."
msgstr ""
"Maksimal grænseområdesgennemsnitlig stigende eller nedvendende bevægelse "
"indenfor BL oprettet af horisontal vindkonvergens. Positiv konvergens er "
"forbundet med lokale småskala-stigende linjer. Negativ konvergens "
"(divergens) producerer nedvendende vertikalt bevægelse, skabende lavniveau-"
"inversioner, hvilket begrænser termikkelyfterhøjder."

